The paper proposes a novel memory network model for question and answering tasks in the context of movie story understanding. The model uses convolutional layers for memory read and write operations, which suggests a focus on natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques. The paper also mentions the model's ability to understand abstract information, which could involve techniques from artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML). The evaluation of the model is based on the MovieQA benchmark, which suggests a focus on information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.IR.
